It's a linker/optimization thing. Don't think there's anything we can do about this and in the end you'd just have to ensure to include the export on your own (as you do now).

On the flip side, you don't really have to link to **sfml-main** anyway; it's just a convenience thing. Just add your own little wrapper `WinMain()` calling `main()`. In the end it's just a trivial call if you don't care about parameters.

    #ifdef WIN32
    #include <Windows.h>
    int WINAPI wWinMain(HINSTANCE, HINSTANCE, PWSTR, int) {
        return main(0, NULL);
    }
    #endif
